survey_response.review_text:
When my husband fainted at home and I rushed him to Max Shalimar Bagh, the very strong team of Cardiology led by Dr. Naveen Bhamri took over the case. 
Not a minute was wasted. All necessary tests were conducted within a matter of hours. 
Dr. Bhamri informed us about the case complications and also the possible treatments available for it. 
His ********* *********, detailed explanations, accompanied by diagrams reassured us that we were in safe hands. 
And while he briefed us about all possible treatments, he allowed us to choose the treatment that we wanted to go for which clearly told us that he is a non-commercial doctor. 
Since ours was a complicated case, he researched and sought the help of other senior Cardiologists like Dr. Balbir Singh for carrying out the surgical procedure. He also lined up at least three back up support teams and necessary infrastructure to ensure that the procedure is carried out successfully. 
Dr. Bhamri personally supervised the post surgery recovery calling up every few hours to check on my husband’s condition. 
Even when we were discharged from the hospital, his office called up to check about my husband’s well being. 
A dynamic combination of dedication, commitment and medical expertise- that’s Dr. Naveen Bhamri for you❗️
Thank you sir for everything❗️ We are eternally grateful to you and your team of Cardiology. 
We are also immensely thankful to Dr. Pankaj, Dr. Gaurav, Dr. Sudhanshu and Dr. Aggarwal for guiding us, treating us and motivating us. 
Thank you Doctors🙏🏻
Gagan and Shruti Gupta 
Delhi

** ** *** ** *** **** *** ****** An amazing doctor not only for the treatment he gave but also for the comfort he shared with the family in testing times.
 Dr.Bhamri treated my mother for Aortic Valve replacement (TAVI process), a critical case but handled exceptionally well by him. The support team including Mr Sumit was very cooperative and handled all our queries very well and ensured we don not have any issues during the process. 
Many thanks Dr. NAVEEN BHAMRI.

Hello Dr. Naveen Bhamri,Just wanted to acknowledge your efforts in the recent angioplasty procedure for my 60 years old mom this month.I kept dreading after her first heart attack in US this June 2022. Back then, we went to one of the renowned heart hospital in New Jersey for the angioplasty which didn't really get successful due to 100% blockage. After reaching back to India, every day was so difficult with my mom in terms of walking, breathing etc., making us pursue again the angioplasty at one of the top notch hospital  in cardiology at national level.The doctors over there too weren't really able to place stents due to 100% blockage. We lost all hopes and have almost accepted the fate of multiple medicines paralleled with side effects for the entire life.That was the time when we got to know about you Dr. Naveen Bhamri (Max, Shalimar Bhagh - Delhi). You and your team have strategized the procedure and on the final day (15 Nov 2022) enagaged for close to two hours and made the impossible as 'successfully possible'. You have solved the problem while minimizing the risk.My mom is really lucky to have your hands on her heart problem.  She at times refer you as the "King of Hearts" and never gets tired admiring your nature and intellect. Many thanks Dr. Naveen Bhamri for all the good work you have been doing in this critical field of Medical Science.Regards,Dr. Rohit GuptaSonipat, Haryana

review_reply.reply_text: Thankyou soo much for your kind words 🙏🙏

I was suffering from severe chest pain. One of my reletive suggested me For Dr Bhamri. We rushed to them in emergency. there whole team started the life saving process, not a single miniute was wasted. Dr Bhamri and his team is very polite and understanding. They have done my angiography. I have a clot in on of artry they removed the clot without any stenting. Never seen a doctor like him who really understands the patient’s problem and don’t do any unnecessary stenting.
Dr Bhamri’s team was also very helpfull Dr Sumit Rana and Mr Amit Kumar they both helped us alot and calm down my family. 
Thank you soo much Dr Bhamri and his team.

Regards 
Naman Jain

We all are very grateful to Dr Naveen Bhamri for treating my mother , I would like to describe that Dr Naveen was a thorough professional in explaning to us about the problem and how he will deal with it as we were all from a non medico background ...he did an excellent job of angioplasty as my mother had a very complex and complicated case but Dr Naveen handled it with his extreme professionalism and I would like to add he s the best in Delhi ..no doubt or second thoughts about it ..would highly recommend him .
I would also like to thanks his staff .. especially Roma and Sumit.. they were ever so helpful all the time .

Dr. Naveen Bhamri is very patient centric and humble doctor. I have taken my mother to MAX Shalimar Bagh for angiography. She is already a heart patient with a stent in her heart. Dr. Bhamri informed us about the case complications and also the possible treatments available for it. His excellent diagnosis including referring of old treatment disc during angiography, understanding of the complete case, detailed explanations with all possible images reassured us that we are taking the right decision and my mother is in the safe hands. He gives ample of time to his patients and looks into each and every detail to ensure his patients get the best of care and treatment.
Dr Bhamri and his team is very polite, committed, helpful and has medical expertise. Mr. Amit helped us a lot in hospital processes.
Thank you so much sir!!

My father complained of severe chest pain & was suggested angiography after echo. We came to know about Dr.Bhamri from my colleague's great experience with him so we went there and we were treated with utmost promptness by Dr.Bhamri's staff. Major obstruction was found on both of the sides during angiography which was to be treated urgently & on priority as noticed by me as well. It was a life threatening condition & i still get scared while thinking about it.
I am thankful to Dr.Bhamri & his team as because of their expertise in the field they were able to normalize the condition & gave the joy back to us.
Thank you so much Sir!!

My father is a coronary artery disease patient on dialysis. His AV fistula and permcath were not working and he had no alternative for Dialysis. His Permcath in neck region was stuck in the vessel and since he had a permanent pacemaker in left side of  chest, it was difficult to take out the defunct Permcath. Dr Bhamri helped us in this difficult situation and took out the old Permcath and inserted a new Permcath in the same region. He did this while keeping us apprised of the situation as well as the risks associated with it. We are grateful to him for helping my father.

I had consulted Dr.Naveen Bhamri for my mother’s peripheral vascular insufficiency problem.he explained overall condition and treatment plan to us.As my mother’s problem was chronic it was a bit complicated case but thanks to dr.bhamri and his team,the angioplasty had been done and the results are excellent.with each passing day my mother’s condition is improving,earlier she was not even able to walk but now she is able to walk and do all the daily activities.All this is because of Dr.Bhamri..Thank u sir....
